quran[564]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,Concerning what they are disputing
  78,2,Concerning the great announcement
  78,3,About which they cannot agree
  78,4,Indeed they will soon come to know
  78,5,"Again, indeed they will soon come to know"
  78,6,Have We not made the earth as a wide expanse
  78,7,And the mountains as pegs
  78,8,And created you mates
  78,9,And made your sleep for rest
  78,10,And made the night as a covering
  78,11,And made the day as a means of subsistence
  78,12,And built over you the seven firmaments
  78,13,And placed a light of splendor
  78,14,And do We not send down from the clouds water in abundance
  78,15,That We may produce with it grains and vegetables
  78,16,And gardens of luxurious growth
  78,17,Indeed the day of sorting out is a thing appointed
  78,18,"The day the trumpet will be sounded, and you will come forth in crowds"
  78,19,And the heavens will be opened as if there were doors
  78,20,"And the mountains will vanish, as if they were a mirage"
  78,21,Truly hell is a place of ambush
  78,22,For the transgressors a place of destination
  78,23,They will dwell therein for ages
  78,24,"Nothing cool will they taste therein, nor any drink"
  78,25,"Except a boiling fluid, and a fluid dark, murky, intensely cold"
  78,26,A fitting reward
  78,27,Because they feared not any account for their deeds
  78,28,And they treated Our signs as false
  78,29,All things have We preserved on record
  78,30,"So taste this, for no increase will We grant you, except in punishment"
  78,31,Indeed for the righteous there will be a fulfillment of their desires
  78,32,"Gardens enclosed, and grapevines"
  78,33,Companions of equal age
  78,34,"And a cup, full"
  78,35,"No vanity will they hear therein, nor lies"
  78,36,"Reward from your Lord, a gift sufficient"
  78,37,"From the Guardian Evolver of the heavens and the earth, and all between. God, the Merciful Benefactor, none will have power to argue with Him"
  78,38,"The day the Spirit and the Angels will stand forth in ranks. None will speak except those permitted by God, the Merciful Benefactor, and he will say what is true"
  78,39,"That day will be the true reality. Therefore, whoever wills, let him anticipate the return to his Lord"
  78,40,"Indeed, We have warned you of a penalty near, the day when humanity will see that which their hands have sent forth, and the unbeliever will say, “Oh my God, I wish that I were mere dust.”"
  79,1,By those who tear it out with violence
  79,2,By those who gently draw it out
  79,3,And by those who glide along
  79,4,Then press forward as in a race
  79,5,And plan to do it
  79,6,One day all that can be in commotion will be in violent commotion
  79,7,Followed by repeated commotions
  79,8,Hearts that day will be in agitation
  79,9,Their eyes will be caste down
  79,10,"They say, “What, will we indeed be returned to our former state"
  79,11,"“What, when we will have become decayed bones?”"
  79,12,"They say, “It would, in that case, be a return with loss.”"
  79,13,"But indeed, it will be but a single cry"
  79,14,"When behold, they will be in the awakening"
  79,15,Has the story of Moses reached you
  79,16,"Behold, your Lord called to him in the sacred valley of Tuwa"
  79,17,"“Go to Pharaoh, for he has indeed transgressed all bounds"
  79,18,"“And say to him, ‘Do you want to be purified"
  79,19,"“And that I guide you to your Lord, so you can fear Him?”"
  79,20,Then Moses showed him the great sign
  79,21,But he rejected it and did not follow
  79,22,"Further, he turned his back, striving hard"
  79,23,Then he gathered them and made a proclamation
  79,24,"Saying, “I am your Lord, Most High”"
  79,25,"But God punished him, and made an example of him, in the hereafter, and in the present life"
  79,26,Indeed in this is an instructive warning for whoever is conscious of God
  79,27,"What, are you more difficult to create or the heaven? God has constructed it"
  79,28,"And on high has He raised its canopy, and He has given it order and perfection"
  79,29,"Its night does He endow with darkness, and its splendor does He bring out"
  79,30,"And the earth, moreover, has He extended"
  79,31,He draws out from there its moisture and its pasture
  79,32,And the mountains has He firmly fixed
  79,33,For use and convenience for you and your livestock
  79,34,"Therefore, when there comes the great overwhelming event"
  79,35,The day when humanity will remember all that they strove for
  79,36,"And hellfire will be placed in full view, for all to see"
  79,37,Then for those who transgressed all bounds
  79,38,And had preferred the life of the present
  79,39,The abode will be hellfire
  79,40,"And for those who had entertained the fear of standing before their Lord, and have restrained their soul from lower desires"
  79,41,Their abode will be the garden
  79,42,"They ask you about the Hour, “When will its appointed time be?”"
  79,43,Are you concerned with the declaration of it
  79,44,With your Lord is the finale
  79,45,You are only a warner for those who fear it
  79,46,"The day they see it, it will be as if they had stayed but a single evening, or until the following morn"
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,Because there came to him the blind man
  80,3,But how could you know whether he might be purified
  80,4,"Or that he might receive advice, and the teaching might profit him"
  80,5,As for one who regards Himself as self-sufficient
  80,6,To him you attend
  80,7,Though it is no blame on you if he grows not
  80,8,But as to him who came to you striving earnestly
  80,9,And with consciousness
  80,10,Of him were you unmindful
  80,11,"By no means should this be so, for it is indeed a message of instruction"
  80,12,"So whosoever wills, may ponder it"
  80,13,In books held in honor
  80,14,Exalted and purified
  80,15,By the hands of scribes
  80,16,"Honorable, pious and just"
  80,17,"Woe to humanity, what has made them reject God"
  80,18,From what has He created them
  80,19,"From a zygote, He has created him, and then molds them in due proportions"
  80,20,Then He makes his path smooth for him
  80,21,"Then He causes him to die, and puts him in his grave"
  80,22,"Then, when it is His will, He will raise him up"
  80,23,By no means has he fulfilled what God has asked of him
  80,24,Then let the human being look at his food
  80,25,And that We pour out water in abundance
  80,26,And We split the earth into pieces
  80,27,And produce therein corn
  80,28,Grapes and nutritious plants
  80,29,Olives and dates
  80,30,"And enclosed gardens, dense with lofty trees"
  80,31,And fruits and fodder
  80,32,For use and convenience for you and your livestock
  80,33,Then when there comes the deafening noise
  80,34,The day one will flee from his own brother
  80,35,And from his mother and his father
  80,36,And from his wife and children
  80,37,"Each one of them, that day, will have enough concern to make him indifferent to the others"
  80,38,Some faces that day will be beaming
  80,39,"Laughing, rejoicing"
  80,40,And other faces that day will be dust-stained
  80,41,Darkness will cover them
  80,42,"Such will be the rejecters of God, the immoral"
  81,1,When the sun is folded up
  81,2,"When the stars fall, losing their luster"
  81,3,When the mountains vanish
  81,4,"When the she-camels, ten months with young, are left untended"
  81,5,When the wild creatures are herded together
  81,6,When the oceans are made to overflow
  81,7,When the souls are sorted out
  81,8,When the female infant buried alive is asked
  81,9,For what crime she was killed
  81,10,When the scrolls are laid open
  81,11,When the world on high is unveiled
  81,12,When the blazing fire is kindled to a fierce blaze
  81,13,And when the garden is brought near
  81,14,Then will each soul know what it has put forward
  81,15,So indeed I call to witness the planets that recede
  81,16,Go straight or hide
  81,17,And the night as it disappears
  81,18,And the dawn as it breathes away the darkness
  81,19,Indeed it is the word of an honorable messenger
  81,20,"Endued with power, with rank before the Lord of the throne"
  81,21,"With authority there, and faithful to his trust"
  81,22,And your companion is not one possessed
  81,23,And without doubt he saw him on the clear horizon
  81,24,He neither grudgingly withholds knowledge of the unknown
  81,25,Nor is it the word of Satan
  81,26,So where are you going
  81,27,Indeed it is no less than a message to all the worlds
  81,28,For whomever among you wills to go straight
  81,29,"But you will not will, except as God wills, the Lord of all the worlds"
  82,1,When the universe is ripped apart
  82,2,When the stars are scattered
  82,3,When the oceans are made to gush forth
  82,4,And when the graves are turned upside down
  82,5,Then each soul will know what it has sent forward and what it has kept back
  82,6,"O human being, what has seduced you from your Guardian Evolver, the Most Honorable"
  82,7,"He Who created you, fashioned you and balanced you"
  82,8,"In whatever form He wills, He puts you together"
  82,9,"No, you reject right and judgment"
  82,10,But indeed over you are appointed angels to protect you
  82,11,"Kind and honorable, writing"
  82,12,They know all that you do
  82,13,"As for the righteous, they will be in bliss"
  82,14,"And as for the wicked, they will be in the fire"
  82,15,Which they will enter on the Day of Accountability
  82,16,And they will not be able to stay away from it
  82,17,And what will explain to you what the Day of Accountability is
  82,18,"Again, what will explain to you what the Day of Accountability is"
  82,19,"The day when no soul will have power to do anything for another, for the decision, that day, will be with God"
  83,1,Shame on those who are unethical
  83,2,"Those who, when they have to receive an amount from others, demand the full amount"
  83,3,"But when they have to give an amount to others, give less than owed"
  83,4,Do they not think that they will be called to account
  83,5,On a mighty day
  83,6,A day when all of humanity will stand before the Lord of all the worlds
  83,7,"No, surely the record of the corrupt is in sijjin"
  83,8,And what will explain to you what sijjin is
  83,9,It is a register inscribed
  83,10,"Woe that day, to those who deny it"
  83,11,Those who deny the Day of Accountability
  83,12,"And none deny it but every transgressor beyond bounds, those who are corrupt"
  83,13,"When Our signs are rehearsed to him, he says, “Tales of the ancients.”"
  83,14,"By no means, but on their hearts is the stain of that which they do"
  83,15,"Indeed, from their Lord that day, they will be veiled"
  83,16,"Further, they will enter the fire of hell"
  83,17,"Further, it will be said to them, “This is that which you rejected as false"
  83,18,"No, indeed the record of the righteous is in illiyin"
  83,19,And what will explain to you what illiyin is
  83,20,It is a register inscribed
  83,21,To which those nearest bear witness
  83,22,Truly the righteous will be in bliss
  83,23,"From on thrones, they observe"
  83,24,You will recognize in their faces the beaming brightness of bliss
  83,25,"Their thirst will be quenched with natural juice, sealed"
  83,26,"The seal of it will be musk, and for this let those aspire who have aspirations"
  83,27,With it will be a mixture of tasnim
  83,28,"A spring, from which those nearest to God will drink"
  83,29,Those in sin used to laugh at those who believed
  83,30,"And whenever they passed by them, they used to wink at each other"
  83,31,"And when they returned to their people, they would return joking"
  83,32,"And whenever they saw them, they would say, “Behold, these are indeed people astray.”"
  83,33,But they had not been sent as keepers over them
  83,34,"But on this day, the believers will laugh at the unbelievers"
  83,35,On thrones they will observe
  83,36,Will the unbelievers not have been paid back for what they did
  84,1,When the universe is ripped apart
  84,2,"And it listens to its Guardian Evolver, as it must"
  84,3,And when the earth is flattened out
  84,4,And casts up what is within it and becomes empty
  84,5,"And listens to its Lord, as it must"
  84,6,"O human beings, indeed you are toiling on towards your Lord, ever toiling, but you will meet Him"
  84,7,Then he who is given his record in his right hand
  84,8,Soon his account will be taken by an easy reckoning
  84,9,And he will turn to his people rejoicing
  84,10,But he who is given his record behind his back
  84,11,Soon he will cry for perdition
  84,12,And he will enter a blazing fire
  84,13,"Indeed he went about among his people, rejoicing"
  84,14,Indeed he thought that he would not have to return to Us
  84,15,"No, no, for his Lord was watchful of him"
  84,16,So I call to witness the ruddy glow of sunset
  84,17,The night and its homing
  84,18,And the moon in its fullness
  84,19,You will surely travel from stage to stage
  84,20,What then is the matter with them that they do not believe
  84,21,"And when the Quran is read to them, they do not fall prostrate"
  84,22,But instead the unbelievers reject it
  84,23,But God has full knowledge of what they hide
  84,24,So announce to them a terrible penalty
  84,25,"Except to those who believe and do righteous deeds, for them is a reward that will never fail"
  85,1,"By the sky, displaying the constellations"
  85,2,By the promised day
  85,3,"By one who witnesses, and the subject of the witness"
  85,4,Woe to the makers of the pit
  85,5,The fire supplied with fuel
  85,6,"Behold, they sat over against the fire"
  85,7,And they witnessed all that they were doing against the believers
  85,8,"And they treated them wrongfully for no other reason than that they believed in God, the All Mighty, the Praiseworthy"
  85,9,"Him to Whom belongs the control of the heavens and the earth, and God is witness to all things"
  85,10,"Those who persecute or draw into temptation the believers, men and women, and do not turn in repentance, will have the penalty of hell. They will have the penalty of the burning fire"
  85,11,"For those who believe and do righteous deeds, will be gardens with rivers flowing through them. That is the great salvation"
  85,12,Truly strong is the Grip of your Lord
  85,13,It is He Who originates and repeats
  85,14,"And He is the Oft-Forgiving, Full of Loving-Kindness"
  85,15,Lord of the throne of glory
  85,16,Doer of all that He intends
  85,17,"Has the story reached you, of the forces"
  85,18,Of Pharaoh and the Thamud
  85,19,And yet the unbelievers persist in rejecting
  85,20,But God encompasses them from behind
  85,21,"No, this is a glorious Quran"
  85,22,On material preserved
  86,1,By the galaxy and the night visitant
  86,2,And what will explain to you what the night-visitant is
  86,3,It is the star of piercing brightness
  86,4,There is no soul that does not have a protector over it
  86,5,Now let the human being think about from what he is created
  86,6,He is created from a drop emitted
  86,7,Proceeding from between the backbone and the ribs
  86,8,Surely God is able to bring him back
  86,9,The day that all things secret will be tested
  86,10,They will have no power and no helper
  86,11,By the firmament which returns
  86,12,And by the earth which cracks open
  86,13,Behold this is the word that is decisive
  86,14,It is not a thing for entertainment
  86,15,"As for them, they are plotting a scheme"
  86,16,But I am devising a plan
  86,17,Therefore grant respite to the unbelievers. Give respite to them for a while
  87,1,Glory to the name of your Lord Most High
  87,2,"Who has created, and further gives order and proportion"
  87,3,"Who has ordained laws, and granted guidance"
  87,4,And Who makes the pasture grow
  87,5,And then makes it dark stubble
  87,6,"By degrees We will teach you to declare the message, so you will not forget"
  87,7,"Except what God wills, for He knows what is manifest and what is hidden"
  87,8,And We will ease you to what is easy
  87,9,"Therefore give advice, in case the advice profits"
  87,10,The advice will be received by those who are conscious of God
  87,11,But it will be avoided by the most unfortunate ones
  87,12,Who will enter the great fire
  87,13,In which they will then neither die nor live
  87,14,But those will flourish who refine themselves
  87,15,And glorify the name of their Lord in prayer
  87,16,"No, you prefer the life of the present"
  87,17,But the hereafter is better and longer lasting
  87,18,And this is in the Ancient Books
  87,19,The Books of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Has the story reached you of the overwhelming event
  88,2,Some faces that day will be humiliated
  88,3,Laboring hard
  88,4,While they are entering the blazing fire
  88,5,"While they are given drink, from a boiling hot spring"
  88,6,No food will there be for them but a bitter Dhari’
  88,7,That will neither nourish nor satisfy hunger
  88,8,Faces that day will be joyful
  88,9,Pleased with their striving
  88,10,In a garden on high
  88,11,Where they will hear no vanity
  88,12,There will be a bubbling spring
  88,13,There will be thrones raised on high
  88,14,Goblets placed
  88,15,And cushions set in rows
  88,16,And rich carpets spread out
  88,17,"Do they not look at the camels, how they are made"
  88,18,"And at the sky, how it is raised high"
  88,19,"And at the mountains, how they are firmly fixed"
  88,20,"And at the earth, how it is spread out"
  88,21,"Therefore give advice, for you are one to advise"
  88,22,You are not one to manage their affairs
  88,23,But if any turn away and reject God
  88,24,God will punish him with a mighty punishment
  88,25,To Us will be their return
  88,26,Then it will be for Us to call them to account
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,By the ten nights
  89,3,By the even and odd
  89,4,And by the night when it passes away
  89,5,Is there not in these an oath for those who understand
  89,6,Do you not see how your Lord dealt with the ‘Ad
  89,7,"Of Iram, with lofty pillars"
  89,8,The like of which were not produced in all the land
  89,9,"And with the Thamud, who carved out rocks in the valley"
  89,10,"And with Pharaoh, lord of stakes"
  89,11,All of these transgressed beyond bounds in the lands
  89,12,And spread corruption therein
  89,13,Therefore your Lord poured on them a scourge of diverse chastisements
  89,14,For your Lord is on a watchtower
  89,15,"Now, as for humanity, when their Lord tries them, giving them honor and gifts, they then say, “My Lord has honored me.”"
  89,16,"But when He tries them, restricting subsistence from them, he says then, “My Lord has humiliated me.”"
  89,17,"But no, you do not honor the orphans"
  89,18,Nor do you encourage one another to feed the poor
  89,19,"And you devour inheritance, all with greed"
  89,20,And you love wealth with inordinate love
  89,21,"No, when the earth is pounded to powder"
  89,22,"And your Lord comes, and His angels, rank upon rank"
  89,23,"And hell, that day, is brought forth, on that day will the human being remember, but how will that remembrance profit him"
  89,24,"He will say, “I wish that I had invested in my life.”"
  89,25,"For that day, their chastisement will be such as none else can inflict"
  89,26,And His bonds will be such as none other can bind
  89,27,"To the righteous soul it will be said, “O you soul in complete rest and satisfaction"
  89,28,"“Come back to your Lord, well pleased, and well-pleasing"
  89,29,“Enter then among My devotees
  89,30,"“Yes, enter My paradise"
  90,1,I call to witness this city
  90,2,And you are free in this city
  90,3,As are the parent and child
  90,4,Indeed We have created the human being into toil and struggle
  90,5,Do they think that none has power over them
  90,6,"They may say, “Wealth have I accumulated in abundance"
  90,7,Does he think that no one sees him
  90,8,Have We not made for him a pair of eyes
  90,9,"And a tongue, and a pair of lips"
  90,10,And shown him the two highways
  90,11,But he has made no rush to the path that is steep
  90,12,And what will explain to you the path that is steep
  90,13,It is freeing the captive
  90,14,Or giving food in a day of hunger
  90,15,To the orphan who claims relationship
  90,16,Or to the indigent down in the dust
  90,17,"Then will he be of those who believe, and encourage patience, and encourage deeds of kindness and compassion"
  90,18,These are the companions of the right hand
  90,19,"But those who reject Our signs, they are the companions of the left hand"
  90,20,On them will be fire vaulted all around
  91,1,By the sun and its splendor
  91,2,By the moon as it follows it
  91,3,By the day as it shows its glory
  91,4,By the night as it conceals it
  91,5,By the firmament and its structure
  91,6,By the earth and its expanse
  91,7,"By the soul, and the proportion and order given to it"
  91,8,And its enlightenment as to its difficulty and its consciousness
  91,9,Certainly she succeeds who purifies it
  91,10,And she fail who corrupts it
  91,11,The Thamud rejected through their inordinate wrongdoing
  91,12,"Behold, their representative was the most terrible person among them"
  91,13,"But the messenger of God said to them, “It is a she-camel of God, so let it have a drink.”"
  91,14,"Then they rejected him, and they hamstrung it. So their Lord, on account of their crime, obliterated their traces and leveled them"
  91,15,And for Him is no fear of its consequences
  92,1,By the night as it conceals
  92,2,By the day as it appears in glory
  92,3,By the creation of male and female
  92,4,"Indeed, what you strive for is diverse"
  92,5,So he who gives and is conscious of God
  92,6,And testifies to the best
  92,7,We will indeed make smooth for him the path to bliss
  92,8,But he who suffers from greed and thinks himself self-sufficient
  92,9,And denies the best
  92,10,We will indeed make smooth for him the path to misery
  92,11,Nor will his wealth profit him when he falls headlong
  92,12,Indeed We take upon Ourselves to guide
  92,13,And indeed to Us belong the end and the beginning
  92,14,Therefore I warn you of a fire blazing fiercely
  92,15,None will reach it but the most unfortunate ones
  92,16,Who give the lie to truth and turn their backs
  92,17,But those most devote will be removed far from it
  92,18,Those who give their wealth for self-purification
  92,19,"And have in their minds no favor from anyone, for which a reward is expected in return"
  92,20,But only the desire to seek for the Countenance of their Lord Most High
  92,21,And soon will they attain satisfaction
  93,1,By the glorious morning light
  93,2,And by the night when it is still
  93,3,"Your Lord has not abandoned you, nor is He displeased"
  93,4,And indeed the future will be better for you than the present
  93,5,And soon your Lord will give you that with which you will be well pleased
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan and give you shelter
  93,7,"And He found you wandering, and He gave you guidance"
  93,8,"And He found you in need, and made you independent"
  93,9,"Therefore, treat not the orphan with harshness"
  93,10,Nor refuse the petitioner
  93,11,"But the bounty of your Lord, proclaim"
  94,1,Have We not expanded your chest
  94,2,And removed from you your burden
  94,3,Which galled your back
  94,4,And raised high the esteem you are held
  94,5,"So indeed, with every difficulty there is relief"
  94,6,"Indeed, with every difficulty there is relief"
  94,7,"Therefore, when you are free, still labor hard"
  94,8,And turn all of your attention to your Lord
  95,1,By the fig and the olive
  95,2,And Mount Sinai
  95,3,And this city of security
  95,4,We have indeed created the human being in the best of forms
  95,5,Then We debase them to the lowest of the low
  95,6,"Except those who believe and do righteous deeds, for they will have a reward unfailing"
  95,7,"Then what can, after this, deceive you about the judgment"
  95,8,Is not God the Wisest of Judges
  96,1,"Read, in the name of your Lord who created"
  96,2,Created the human being from a zygote
  96,3,"Proclaim, and your Lord is Most Bountiful"
  96,4,He Who taught the use of the pen
  96,5,Taught the human being that which he knew not
  96,6,"No, but the human being transgresses all bounds"
  96,7,When he looks upon himself as self-sufficient
  96,8,"Indeed, to your Lord is the return"
  96,9,Do you see one who forbids
  96,10,A worshipper when he turns to pray
  96,11,Have you seen whether he has guidance
  96,12,Or encourages righteousness
  96,13,Do you see if he denies and turns away
  96,14,Does he not know that God sees
  96,15,"Let him beware, that if he does not desist, We will drag him by the hair of his head"
  96,16,"His lying, sinful head"
  96,17,Then let him call to his advisers
  96,18,We will call on the angels of punishment
  96,19,"No, do not follow, but bow down in adoration, and bring yourself ever closer"
  97,1,We have indeed revealed it in the Night of Power
  97,2,And what will explain to you what the Night of Power is
  97,3,The Night of Power is as good as a thousand months
  97,4,"There comes down the angels and the spirit by God's permission, for every will"
  97,5,"Peace, until the rise of morn"
  98,1,Those who reject it among the people of the Book and among the polytheists were not going to depart until there came to them clear evidence
  98,2,"A messenger from God, rehearsing scriptures kept pure"
  98,3,"In it are laws, right and straight"
  98,4,"Nor did the people of the Book form sects, until after there came to them clear evidence"
  98,5,"And they have been asked no more than this— to worship God, offer Him sincere devotion, be truthful, establish prayer, and give zakat, and that is the way of life which is right and straight"
  98,6,"Those who reject it among the people of the Book and among the polytheists, will be in hellfire, to dwell therein forever. They are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,"Those who have faith and do righteous deeds, they are the best of creatures"
  98,8,"Their reward with God is gardens of eternity, beneath which rivers flow, they will dwell therein forever, God well pleased with them, and they with Him. All this for those who are conscious of their Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is shaken to its utmost convulsion
  99,2,And the earth throws up its burden
  99,3,"And the human being yells, “What is the matter with it?”"
  99,4,On that day it will declare its information
  99,5,Because your Lord would have given it inspiration
  99,6,"On that day, humanity will proceed in groups sorted out, to be shown their deeds"
  99,7,Then anyone who has done an atom’s weight of good see it
  99,8,And anyone who has done an atom’s weight of wrong will see it
  100,1,By those who race with panting breath
  100,2,And strike sparks of fire
  100,3,And push home the charge in the morning
  100,4,And raise the dust in clouds
  100,5,And move forward en masse
  100,6,Truly the human being is ungrateful to their Guardian Evolver
  100,7,And to that they bear witness
  100,8,And violent is their love of wealth
  100,9,"Does he not know, when that which is in the graves is scattered abroad"
  100,10,And that which is in the chest is made manifest
  100,11,That their Guardian Evolver had been well acquainted with them that day
  101,1,The Disaster
  101,2,What is the Disaster
  101,3,And what will explain to you what the Disaster is
  101,4,It is a day when humanity will be like scattered moths
  101,5,And the mountains will be as wool
  101,6,Then he whose scales will be heavy
  101,7,Will be in a life of blessings and satisfaction
  101,8,But he whose scale will be found light
  101,9,Will have his home in a pit
  101,10,And what will explain to you what this is
  101,11,It is a fire blazing fiercely
  102,1,The competition for accumulating diverts you
  102,2,Until you all visit the graves
  102,3,"But no, you will soon know"
  102,4,"Again, you will soon know"
  102,5,"No, were you to know with certainty of mind"
  102,6,You will certainly see hellfire
  102,7,"Again, you will see it with certainty of sight"
  102,8,"Then, you will be questioned that day about the pleasure you indulged in"
  103,1,By time
  103,2,Indeed the human being is lost
  103,3,"Except those who have faith, work to make things right, and join together in the mutual teaching of truth, patience, and constancy"
  104,1,"Woe to every scandalous, backbiter"
  104,2,Who accumulates wealth and counts it
  104,3,Thinking that his wealth will make him last forever
  104,4,By no means. He will surely be thrown into that which breaks into pieces
  104,5,And what will explain to you about that which breaks into pieces
  104,6,It is the fire of God kindled to a blaze
  104,7,That mounts right up to the hearts
  104,8,It will be made into a vault over them
  104,9,"In columns, extended"
  105,1,Do you not see how your Lord dealt with the companions of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their treacherous plan go astray
  105,3,And He sent against them flocks of birds
  105,4,Striking them with stones of baked clay
  105,5,Then He made them like an empty field of stalks and straw which has been eaten
  106,1,For the security enjoyed by the Quraysh
  106,2,Their security covering journeys by winter and summer
  106,3,Let them adore the Guardian Evolver of this house
  106,4,"Who provides them with food against hunger, and with security against fear of danger"
  107,1,Do you see the one who denies the Judgment
  107,2,They are those who repulse the orphan
  107,3,And do not encourage the feeding of the indigent
  107,4,So woe to the worshippers
  107,5,Who are neglectful of their prayers
  107,6,Those who want to be seen
  107,7,But refuse to do even neighborly deeds
  108,1,"To you, We have granted the fountain of abundance"
  108,2,Therefore turn in prayer and sacrifice to your Lord
  108,3,"For he who hates you, he will be cut off"
  109,1,"Say, O you who do not believe"
  109,2,I do not worship that which you worship
  109,3,Nor will you worship that which I worship
  109,4,And I will not worship that which you are accustomed to worshiping
  109,5,Nor will you worship that which I worship
  109,6,"To you your way, and to me, my way"
  110,1,When the help of God and victory comes
  110,2,And you see the people enter God's religion in crowds
  110,3,"Glorify by Praising your Guardian Evolver, and pray for His forgiveness, for He is Oft-Forgiving"
  111,1,"May the hands of the father of the flame perish, and may he perish"
  111,2,"No profit will he have for all his wealth, and all his gains"
  111,3,He will soon burn in a fire of a blazing flame
  111,4,His wife will carry the wood as fuel
  111,5,With a twisted rope of palm-leaf fiber around her neck
  112,1,"Say, He is God, the One and Only"
  112,2,"God, the Eternal, Absolute"
  112,3,"He has no children, nor was He born"
  112,4,And nothing is like Him
  113,1,"Say, I seek refuge with the Guardian Evolver of the dawn"
  113,2,From the harm of created things
  113,3,From the harm of darkness as it overspreads
  113,4,From the harm of those who whisper into convictions
  113,5,And from the harm of the envious one as he practices envy
  114,1,"Say, I seek refuge with the Guardian Evolver of humanity"
  114,2,The King of humanity
  114,3,The God of humanity
  114,4,"From the harm of the whisperer, who withdraws after he whispers"
  114,5,And who whispers into the hearts of humanity
  114,6,Among jinn and humanity